OSmond Earle of Seez in Normandy, was by William Conqueror made Biſhop of Salisbury, & after, the firſt Earle of Dorſet, (as M. Camden hath in his Britannia, pag. 217
   •
) But Milles, in Somerſet Glouers Booke of the ſucceſſions of Earles, pag. 392. hath, that the ſaid Oſmond was Earle of Somerſet; and therefore to which I ſhall giue credite, I leaue to the indifferent Reader.
